    "client_msg_id": "841c063c-408d-400b-a952-2bd5f7649500",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Hi! I recently noticed how I struggle regrouping things by topic/task/project on my different devices (laptop, phone). Quite frequently, one topic can be spread across 5+ apps/website. My less than ideal solution is to introduce another aggregator app (roam research in my case) and paste &amp; tags different links when possible. Arc browser spaces also helps with that. The issue is that it's very manual and not worth for small ad hoc topic and researches.\n\nIs this a problem you are facing? How do you solve/work-around it? Any interesting links on the topic?\n\nI believe it could &amp; should be solved at the OS level and found really interesting project: <https://playb.it/>, MercuryOS, <https://alexanderobenauer.com/labnotes/000/> but I feel like there should be more",
    "user": "U04BFFZNGRY",
    "ts": "1693827492.309929",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "/QbZ",
